about.description: The goal is to enable the use of JupyterLab's themes with pygments-generated HTML.
about.summary: Pygments syntax coloring scheme making use of the JupyterLab CSS variables

name: jupyterlab_pygments
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jupyterlab_pygments" %}
{% set version = "0.1.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 19a0ccde7daddec638363cd3d60b63a4f6544c9181d65253317b2fb492a797b9

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - pygments >=2.4.1,<3

test:
  imports:
    - jupyterlab_pygments

about:
  home: http://github.com/JupyterLab/jupyterlab_pygments
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Pygments syntax coloring scheme making use of the JupyterLab CSS variables'
  description: |
      The goal is to enable the use of JupyterLab's themes with pygments-generated HTML.
  dev_url: https://github.com/JupyterLab/jupyterlab_pygments

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - SylvainCorlay
    - maartenbreddels
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.17
